The paper deals with the transmission of messages over a quantum broadcast channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and quantum information (cs.QI). The paper also discusses the need for secrecy and confidentiality, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of random numbers and the trade-off between message rates suggests a connection to coding theory (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the asymptotic behavior of the bounds, which could be related to statistical learning (cs.SI).
